# Programs tests/run.sh skips, one per line: "<name>  <reason>" (the first
# whitespace-delimited field is the program name; the rest is the reason).
# Blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored.
#
# These three are non-portable across host ISAs. minbasic converts an
# overflowed numeric (machine +Inf, from an overflow / division by zero) to an
# integer index via cast(int, ...), and the result of casting a non-finite /
# out-of-range float to int is platform-dependent: arm64 saturates (+Inf ->
# INT64_MAX), x86-64 yields INT64_MIN. The macOS/arm64-frozen fixtures encode
# the arm64 value, so the programs fail on an x86-64 runner. Tracked in the
# examples repo's TODO.md (the minbasic side) and the binate repo's
# explorations/claude-todo.md (the toolchain cast(int,float) gap). Re-enable
# once the cast semantics are defined.

P168  array subscript from an overflowed expression: Z(A^A), A=9999
P174  TAB column from an overflowed expression: TAB(9^(9^9))
P180  ON-GOTO index from a division-by-zero result: ON 1E-33/0 GOTO ...
